27/01/2004
TIRANA, Albania -- The US Embassy in Tirana issued a statement Monday (26 January) in support of a new task force against organised crime in Albania.
It said US authorities would back and promote the panel in any way that they could.
The task force was established by virtue of a joint decree signed by Minister of Public Order Igli Toska and Prosecutor General Theodhori Sollaku.
Under terms of the decree, the task force will include prosecutors and judicial police officers from Tirana, Durres, Shkodra, Fier and Vlora.
(ATA - 26/01/04)
